    ) VALUES (1499855, 'Etravirine', 'Voriconazole', 'Moderate', 'Coadministration of etravirine and voriconazole may result in increased plasma concentrations of both drugs. Etravirine is a substrate of CYP450 2C19, 2C9 and 3A4 as well as an inhibitor of CYP450 2C19 and 2C9, while voriconazole is a substrate of CYP450 2C19 and inhibitor of CYP450 2C19, 2C9 and 3A4. Theoretically, etravirine can inhibit the metabolism of voriconazole via CYP450 2C19, and voriconazole can inhibit the metabolism of etravirine via CYP450 2C19, 2C9 and 3A4.', NULL, 'Because safety data regarding increased etravirine exposures are limited, caution is advised if etravirine is prescribed in combination with voriconazole.', NULL, 'Because safety data regarding increased etravirine exposures are limited, caution is advised if etravirine is prescribed in combination with voriconazole. Dosage adjustments may be required for one or both drugs if undue adverse effects occur.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317477);
